			<sumFormula>Not Available</sumFormula>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Fermented dairy products, such as buttermilk, yogurt, and kefir, have unique bioactive proteins and provide nutrients like calcium and protein. They have a longer shelf life and are less prone to spoilage than nonfermented food products. These products have been used for thousands of years to preserve milk, make it more transportable, less perishable, readily available, and more digestible due to lactose breakdown during the fermentation process. They may reduce heart disease risk and aid digestion, immunity, and weight loss. They are also linked to reduced risk for Type 2 diabetes.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">发酵乳制品，如酪乳、酸奶和克菲尔，具有独特的生物活性蛋白质，并提供像钙和蛋白质这样的营养素。它们的保质期更长，比非发酵食品更不容易变质。这些产品已经被使用了数千年来保存牛奶，使其更易于运输，不易腐烂，随时可用，并且由于发酵过程中的乳糖分解，更易于消化。它们可能降低心脏病风险并有助于消化，免疫和减肥。它们还与降低2型糖尿病的风险有关。</common:generalComment>
